    <sectiondef kind="typedef">
      <memberdef kind="typedef" id="group__dma__interface_1gaca9b0a9ed3ffdc84275187e0b05c20d9" prot="public" static="no">
        <type>void(*</type>
        <definition>dma_callback_t</definition>
        <argsstring>)(const struct device *dev, void *user_data, uint32_t channel, int status)</argsstring>
        <name>dma_callback_t</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback function for DMA transfer completion. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If enabled, callback function will be invoked at transfer or block completion, or when an error happens. In circular mode, <computeroutput>status</computeroutput> indicates that the DMA device has reached either the end of the buffer (DMA_STATUS_COMPLETE) or a water mark (DMA_STATUS_BLOCK).</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the DMA device calling the callback. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>user_data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A pointer to some user data or NULL </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>channel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The channel number </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>status</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Status of the transfer<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>DMA_STATUS_COMPLETE buffer fully consumed</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>DMA_STATUS_BLOCK buffer consumption reached a configured block or water mark</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>A negative errno otherwise </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/drivers/dma.h" line="191" column="9" bodyfile="zephyr/drivers/dma.h" bodystart="191" bodyend="-1"/>
